title: Google\Cloud\VideoIntelligence\V1\ObjectTrackingAnnotation
name: ObjectTrackingAnnotation
description:
Annotations corresponding to one tracked object.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.videointelligence.v1.ObjectTrackingAnnotation

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.segment
params.description: Non-streaming batch mode ONLY. Each object track corresponds to one video segment where it appears.

params.name: data.track_id
params.description: Streaming mode ONLY. In streaming mode, we do not know the end time of a tracked object before it is completed. Hence, there is no VideoSegment info returned. Instead, we provide a unique identifiable integer track_id so that the customers can correlate the results of the ongoing ObjectTrackAnnotation of the same track_id over time.

params.name: data.entity
params.description: Entity to specify the object category that this track is labeled as.

params.name: data.confidence
params.description: Object category's labeling confidence of this track.

params.name: data.frames
params.description: Information corresponding to all frames where this object track appears. Non-streaming batch mode: it may be one or multiple ObjectTrackingFrame messages in frames. Streaming mode: it can only be one ObjectTrackingFrame message in frames.
